pl_remarks: dictinction between sapwood and heartwood is not possible in Fagus sylvatica. To calculate tree sapflow from sapflux density we used a species-specific function (see Granier et al 2003. Deciduous forests: carbon and water fluxes, balances and ecophysiological determinants. Ecol. Stud. 163, 55–70.) that gives relative sap flux density as a function of depth below cambium
